
sample_otp_sub: Demonstrate OTP root deletion/obliteration

sample_otp_sub will delete a root created by sample_otp user container.

Create a root for sample_otp_sub and dummy root by loading
sample_otp container:

$ mwtest.py -c 100 run sample_otp.img

$ printf true > test.txt
$ cmtest data -f100 test.txt

Unload the sample_otp container:
$ mwtest.py -c100 unload

Run hard reset command as it is silo container
$ cmtest reset hard

Now load the sample_otp_sub container which will delete the dummy root
created by sample_otp:

$ mwtest.py -c100 run sample_otp_sub.img
$ cmtest data -f100 test.txt

To unload container:
$ mwtest.py -c100 unload
